model_id: Unique identifier for all the PDXs derived from the same tissue sample
name: Most comman name associate with model. Please use the CCLE name if available
type: Type of organoid or cell model
parent_id: Please add the model Id of the model used to generate the model. If the model was not in this set, please refer to it by external id
comments: Add crucial comments about the model that cannot be expressed by other fields
supplier: Please provide the suplies brief acronym or name followed by a colon and thel number or name use to reference the model
external_ids: Depmap accession, Cellusaurus accession or other id. Please place in comma separated list
publications: If model has been part of a published study include pubmed IDs separated by commas.

name: LAMA84_HAEMATOPOIETIC_AND_LYMPHOID_TISSUE
comments: orthotopic

name: free text
type: One of the following: organoid, CRC, 3-D other, cell model
growth_properties: One of the following: embedded 3d culture, adherent, mix of adherent and suspension, suspension
comments: heterotopic, orthotopic, not collected, or not provided.
supplier: free text , not collected or not provided

name: essential
comments: essential

name: SK-N-SH
comments: SH-SY5Y is a thrice cloned (SK-N-SH -> SH-SY -> SH-SY5 -> SH-SY5Y) subline of the neuroblastoma cell line SK-N-SH (ATCC).

name: MDA-MB-435S
comments: MDA-MB-435 and its variant MDA-MB435S have been found to be cross contaminated with M14 (ICLAC, DOI: 10.1002/ijc.31067)

name: P3HR-1
comments:
P3HR-1 is a clonally derived subline of Jiyoye.
2B8 is a HAT sensitive fusion cell line derived from the P3HR-1 (ATCC).

name: LN-319
comments: LN-319 was found to be a derivative of LN-992. (PubMed=22570425).

name: MC-CAR-Z2
comments: MC-CAR-Z2 is a derivative of MC-CAR (ATCC).

name: Mac-1
comments:
MAC-1, MAC-2A & MAC-2B were all derived from the same patient. (10.1056/NEJM199204233261704).
Mac-1 was derived in 1985 from circulating Sézary-like cells in the peripheral blood.
Mac-2A and Mac-2B were started from separate skin-tumor nodules in 1987.

name: NCI-H513
comments: NCI-H125 and NCI-H513 have been show to be cross contaminated (ATCC, ICLAC)

name: D-542MG
comments: L542 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as D-542MG.

name: COLO-794
comments:
COLO-818 has been shown to come from the same patient as COLO-800 (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.25242.)
COLO-800 and COLO-794 were both derived from the same patient (ECACC).

name: PaCaDD-159
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: MY
comments: MY-M12 is the subclone of the MY (JCRB).

name: 451Lu
comments: 451Lu is a selected xenograft aggressive metastatic sub-line of WM164 (Rockland).

name: PEO23
comments:
PEO14, PEO23 and TO14 were derived from the same patient. (PMID: 3167863).
PEO14 and PEO23 samples were obtained from ascites, PEO14 prior to therapy and PEO23 following chemotherapy.
TO14 was derived from a solid metastasis in the omentum.

name: LAMA-84
comments: LAMA-87 is a subclone of LAMA-84 obtained after subcutaneous transplantation of LAMA-84 cells into estrone-treated nude mice (DSMZ).

name: RH-18
comments: The RH-18 cell line was generated from a xenograft derived from a tumor from a previously untreated 2-year-old patient with a perineal RMS assigned as embryonal histology. (PMID: 23882450).

name: RT-112
comments: RT112-84 and RT-112 share common ancestry (DSMZ, ECACC).

name: SCMC-RM2-1
comments: SCMC-RM2-1 is a sub-clone of SCMC-RM2. (PMID: 23882450).

name: L542
comments: L542 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as D-542MG.

name: EFM-192C
comments: EFM-192B and EFM-192C were established from the same patient as EFM-192A (DSMZ).

name: NCI-H1770
comments: NCI-BL1770 is a lymphoblastoid line established from the same patient as NCI-H1770 (ATCC).

name: HCC1428-BL
comments: HCC1428-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as the breast carcinoma cell line HCC1428 (ATCC).

name: C3A
comments: C3A is clonal derivative of Hep-G2 that was selected for strong contact inhibition of growth, high albumin production, high production of alpha fetoprotein (AFP) and ability to grow in glucose deficient medium (ATCC).

name: ML-1
comments: The ML-1, ML-2, and ML-3 lines were all established from the peripheral blood samples obtained from the same patient with acute myeloid leukemia (PMID: 3458526).

name: COLO-201
comments:
COLO-201, COLO-205 and COLO-206F were all established from the ascites fluid of a patient with adenocarcinoma of the colon.
COLO-197 is a lymphoid line established from the original biopsy of the same patient.
COLO-200 is a lymphoid line establisted from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 565251).

name: LB771-HNC
comments: LB771-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB771-HNC.

name: MOLT-14
comments: MOLT-13 and MOLT-14 are simultaneous sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: HMCB
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: KLM-1
comments:
KLM-1 and RPK-1 were both derived from the PK-1 cell line. 
KLM-1 was generated through injection of PK-1 and tumour formation in nude mice. (RIKEN, PMID: 8872523).
RPK-1 is a gemcitabine resistant sublcone of PK-1. (PMID: 22490663)

name: HEC-1-A
comments:
HEC-1-A was derived from the same patient as HEC-1 (JCRB).
HEC-1-B is a substrain of HEC-1-A (ATCC).

name: PaCaDD-188
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: HCC1954
comments: HCC1954-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated from peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1954 (ATCC).

name: ONCO-DG-1
comments: ONCO-DG-1 is cross-contaminated with cell line OVCAR-3 (DSMZ).

name: COG-AR-382
comments: http://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/68/9_Supplement/3743 COG-AR-359 and COG-AR-382 are derived from the same patient. (http://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/68/9_Supplement/3743).

name: HOS
comments:
HOS and 143B originated from the same patient: 143B is TK- and originated indirectly from HOS which is TK+ (ECACC & PMID: 20544518). 
HTK- and 143B have a common STR profile and are thought to be the same cell line (ECACC).

name: Mero-41
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: MOLT-4
comments: MOLT-4 was derived from the same patient as MOLT-3 (ATCC).

name: GA-10 (Clone 20)
comments: GA-10-Clone-4 and GA-10-Clone-20 are subclones of the GA 10 cell line derived by culturing the parental line on semi solid medium conditioned by a feeder layer (ATCC).

name: Mero-14
comments: Patient has a history of asbestos exposure.

name: HCT-15
comments: DLD-1, HCT-15, HCT-8 and HRT-18 have been shown to have a common genetic origin (ECACC & PMID: 9809040).

name: EFM-192A
comments: EFM-192B and EFM-192C were established from the same patient as EFM-192A (DSMZ).

name: KMS-28-BM
comments: KMS-28-PE and KMS-28-BM were both derived independent samples, pleural effusion and bone marrow, from the same patient (PMID: 11886382).

name: I-2-1
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: BE2-M17
comments:
BE2-M17 is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2.
BE2-C is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2 (ATCC).

name: UT-7-EPO
comments:
UT-7-EPO is an erythropoietin-dependent subline of UT-7 (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V82.2.456.456). 
UT-7-GM is a subline of UT-7 and is a bipotential cell line that can be induced to differentiate into erythroid and megakaryocytic lineages by EPO and TPO (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V89.11.4021). 
UT-7-TPO is a thrombopoietin-dependent subline of UT-7-GM (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V87.11.4552.bloodjournal87114552).

name: 1181N1
comments:
U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC). 
1321N1 is a subclone of 1181N1 which itself is a subclone of U-118 MG  (ECACC).

name: BJ1-hTERT
comments: The hTERT-immortalized foreskin fibroblast cell line, BJ-5ta, was derived by transfecting the BJ foreskin fibroblast cell line with the pGRN145 hTERT-expressing plasmid (ATCC).

name: ML-2
comments: The ML-1, ML-2, and ML-3 lines were all established from the peripheral blood samples obtained from the same patient with acute myeloid leukemia (PMID: 3458526).

name: WM-266-4
comments:
WM115, WM266-4, WM239A and WM165-1 were all derived from the same patient. 
WM115 cell line originated from the primary tumor, and WM239A, WM165-1 and WM266-4 were from individual lymph-node metastases (Rockland).

name: NCI-BL1770
comments: NCI-BL1770 is a lymphoblastoid line established from the same patient as NCI-H1770 (ATCC).

name: NCI-H1870
comments: NCI-H1870 and NCI-H1304 are known syonymous lines (ICLAC).

name: RERF-LC-OK
comments:
SK-MG-1 and Marcus share common ancestry (JCRB).

RERF-LC-OK has been shown to be contaminated with Marcus cell line (ICLAC).

name: HeLa
comments:
HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

name: RH-4
comments: RH-41 and RH-4 were both derived from the same patient sample. (PMID: 23882450)

name: UT-7-GM
comments:
UT-7-EPO is an erythropoietin-dependent subline of UT-7 (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V82.2.456.456). 
UT-7-GM is a subline of UT-7 and is a bipotential cell line that can be induced to differentiate into erythroid and megakaryocytic lineages by EPO and TPO (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V89.11.4021). 
UT-7-TPO is a thrombopoietin-dependent subline of UT-7-GM (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V87.11.4552.bloodjournal87114552).

name: LN-444
comments: LN-443 is a subline of LN-444, and accordingly, both lines contain the same PTEN mutation. (PubMed=22570425).

name: NCOL-1
comments: NCOL-1 has been shown to be derived from LoVo (ICLAC).

name: HA7-RCC
comments: HA7-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as HA7-RCC.

name: ML-3
comments: The ML-1, ML-2, and ML-3 lines were all established from the peripheral blood samples obtained from the same patient with acute myeloid leukemia (PMID: 3458526).

name: NCI-BL2122
comments: NCI-BL2122 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2122 (ATCC).

name: PL45
comments: Panc-10-05 was derived from the same patient as the PL45 cell line (ATCC).

name: FTC-238
comments: FTC-133, FTC-236 and FTC-238 were all derived from the same individual (ECACC).

name: I-9-2
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: EW-2
comments: EW-1 and EW-2 are from the same patient (PMID: 6713356).

name: LB373-EBV
comments: LB373-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB373-MEL, the parental line of LB373-MEL-D.

name: EB-1
comments: SNP and STR profiling by the Sanger and Broad Institute indicate both EB-1 and EB2 share common ancestry.

name: EW-1
comments: EW-1 and EW-2 are from the same patient (PMID: 6713356).

name: COLO-775
comments: COLO-775 has been shown to be a derivitive of RPMI-8226 (ICLAC).

name: NCI-H1881
comments: NCI-H1876 & NCI-H1882 & NCI-H1881 have been derived from the same same patient. (NCI-Navy Medical Oncology Brance Cell Line Supplement DOI: 10.1002/jcb.240630505)

name: 2B8
comments:
P3HR-1 is a clonally derived subline of Jiyoye.
2B8 is a HAT sensitive fusion cell line derived from the P3HR-1 (ATCC).

name: HA7-EBV
comments: HA7-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as HA7-RCC.

name: NCI-H1339
comments: NCI-H1339, NCI-H157, and NCI-H1264 are reported to come from different donors but have matching STR profiles (Yu et al, 2015). ICLAC made contact with the originator's laboratory to discuss the match. They have fresh stocks of NCI-H1339 with the correct fingerprint matching NCI-BL1339, which is a lymphoblastoid cell line from the same donor. (ICLAC v9) NCI-BL1339 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H1339. (PMID: 8806092).

name: Tanoue
comments:
ST is a subclone of Tanoue.
GR-ST is a subclone of ST cells transformed with human G-CSF receptor cDNA (JCRB).

name: BGC-823
comments:
HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

name: U-HO1-PTPN1
comments: U-HO1-PTPN1 was derived from U-HO1 by stable transfection with non-receptor protein-tyrosine phosphatase N1 (PTPN1) (DOI: 10.1186/1471-2121-11-99).

name: RPMI-8226
comments: COLO-775 has been shown to be a derivitive of RPMI-8226 (ICLAC).

name: GA-10
comments: GA-10-Clone-4 and GA-10-Clone-20 are subclones of the GA 10 cell line derived by culturing the parental line on semi solid medium conditioned by a feeder layer (ATCC).

name: MKN74
comments: MKN28 has been shown to be a derivitive of MKN74 (JCRB & ICLAC).

name: K029AX
comments: K029AX was derived from parental line K029. (Cellosaurus).

name: MCC14-1
comments: MCC14-1 & MCC14-2 were both established from the same nodal metastasis. (PMID: 7814141).

name: TE-13
comments: TE-2, TE-3, TE-7, TE-12 & TE-13 share common ancestry (PMID: 17804709)

name: ACCS
comments: ACCS has been shown to be a derivitive of T24 (PMID: 20143388).

name: PC-14
comments: PC-14 has been shown to be a derivitive of PC-9 (RIKEN, ECACC).

name: A375_CJ1
comments: Dabrafenib and Trametinib resistant subclone of A375. A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.

name: TE-3
comments: TE-2, TE-3, TE-7, TE-12 & TE-13 share common ancestry (PMID: 17804709)

name: COLO-684
comments: COLO-685 was established from the same patient as COLO-684 (DSMZ).

name: NCI-BL1339
comments: NCI-BL1339 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H1339. (PMID: 8806092).

name: HCC2157
comments: HCC2157-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC2157 (ATCC).

name: 143B
comments:
HOS and 143B originated from the same patient: 143B is TK- and originated indirectly from HOS which is TK+ (ECACC & PMID: 20544518). 
HTK- and 143B have a common STR profile and are thought to be the same cell line (ECACC).

name: OC-315
comments: OC-314, OC-315 and OC-316 share common ancestry (PMID: 15677628). Sanger and Broad Institute genomic data supports this conclusion for OC-314 & OC-316 (no data has been generated for OC-315).

name: LC-1-sq-SF
comments:
LC-1F (Floating variant) is from the same patient as LC-1-sq (Lung Cancer-1/Squamous). 
LC-1-sq-SF is a variant of LC-1-sq cultured in serum-free media (RIKEN).

name: OVCAR-8
comments: NCI-ADR-RES has been shown to be derivitive of OVCAR-8 (ICLAC)

name: BB65-EBV
comments: BB65-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB65-RCC.

name: Tera-2
comments:
NTERA-2 was established in 1980 from a nude mouse xenograft of the Tera 2 cell line. 
NTERA-2-cl-D1 is a sub-clone of NTERA-2 (ATCC).

name: COV362-4
comments: COV362-4 is a subline of an early passage of the cell line COV362. (ECACC).

name: ICC10-6
comments: ICC10-6 and ICC10-8 were derived from the same individual (DepMap STR).

name: RCC4
comments:
RCC4-emptyvector and RCC4-VHL were derived from the RCC4 cell line by stable transfection with pcDNA3 and pCDNA3-VHL respectively (ECACC). 
SLR24 was shown to be a RCC4 derivative (ICLAC).

name: SKG-II-LUC
comments:
SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: UPCI-SCC-016
comments: UPCI-SCC-026 was derived following recurrance from the same patient as UPCI-SCC-016 (DOI: 10.1016/j.oraloncology.2007.05.003).

name: HCC1143
comments: HCC1143-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated using peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1143 (ATCC).

name: SCMC-RM2
comments: SCMC-RM2-1 is a sub-clone of SCMC-RM2. (PMID: 23882450).

name: H16N2
comments:
21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).

name: Hep-G2
comments: C3A is clonal derivative of Hep-G2 that was selected for strong contact inhibition of growth, high albumin production, high production of alpha fetoprotein (AFP) and ability to grow in glucose deficient medium (ATCC).

name: MM1
comments:
MM1R is a dexamethasone resistant line derived from MM1. 
MM1S is a dexamethasone sensitive line derived from MM1 (ATCC).

name: DLD-1
comments: DLD-1, HCT-15, HCT-8 and HRT-18 have been shown to have a common genetic origin (ECACC & PMID: 9809040).

name: CP50-MEL-B
comments: CP50-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP50-MEL-B.

name: BDCM
comments: Leukaemic cell byproduct of a therapeutic pheresis of a patient with M5a AML (PMID: 12437665)

name: MOR-CPR
comments: MOR/CPR has been developed by growing the parent line, MOR, in increasing concentrations of cisplatin. (ECACC),

name: HCC1954-BL
comments: HCC1954-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated from peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1954 (ATCC).

name: MOLM-13
comments: MOLM-13 and MOLM-14 are sister cell lines, both established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (DSMZ).

name: LB831-BLC
comments: LB831-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB831-BLC.

name: NCI-H1993
comments: NCI-H1993 and NCI-H2073 were derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: BPH-1
comments: Prostate epithelial cells from a 68-year-old man with benign prostate hyperplasia cells were immortalized with SV-40 large T-antigen (DSMZ).

name: WPE1-NA22
comments:
RWPE-2 was derived from RWPE-1 by transformation with Ki-ras using the Kirsten murine sarcoma virus.
RWPE2-W99 cell line was derived from the RWPE-2 by cloning in soft agar to select cells that show high expression of Ki-ras (ATCC). 
WPE1-NA22 cells were derived from RWPE-1 cells by exposure to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (ATCC).

name: OVCAR-3
comments: ONCO-DG-1 is cross-contaminated with cell line OVCAR-3 (DSMZ).

name: HCC1395
comments: HCC1395-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as the breast carcinoma cell line HCC1395 (ATCC).

name: HCC2218
comments: HCC2218-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC2218 (ATCC).

name: Ramos-2G6-4C10
comments: Ramos-2G6-4C10 was derived from the Ramos cell line by repetitive cloning with selection for low constitutive expression of CD23 and maximum stimulation of CD23 expression by IL4 (ATCC).

name: JEG-3
comments:
Hs-630-T has been shown to be a derivative of BeWo (PMID: 25877200, Cellosaurus).
JEG-3 has the same DNA profile as BeWo; it was established by serial cloning of BeWo (ECACC & PMID: 4299001).

name: 21NT
comments:
21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).

name: COLO-829BL
comments:
COLO-829 was derived from a sample taken prior to chemotherapy for metastatic melanoma.
COLO 829BL was established from the same patient by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of a sample of peripheral blood (ATCC).

name: CMK-86
comments:
CMK11-5 is a subclone of CMK (PMID: 1391807).
CMK, CMK-86 and CMK-11-5 share high SNP identity (DOI: 10.1038/nature11003).

name: TE-2
comments: TE-2, TE-3, TE-7, TE-12 & TE-13 share common ancestry (PMID: 17804709)

name: HuG1-N
comments: A variant of HuG1 producing Nagao-type alkaline phosphatase. HuG1-N and HuG1-PI were derived from the parental line HuG1 (JCRB).

name: RMZ
comments: RMZ-RC2 and RMZ-RC5 are clonal cell lines derived from RMZ (DOI: 10.1038/bjc.1986.273).

name: WM793B
comments: 1205Lu was dervied by serial passaging of WM793 through immune deficient mice and harvesting lung metastases (DOI: 10.4172/1948-5956.1000401).

name: A549
comments: JHU-028 has been shown to be cross contaminated with A549 (ICLAC).

name: Hs-888-Sk
comments: Hs-888-Lu and Hs-888-Sk were derived using normal tissue from the same patient as the metastatically derived tumour cell line Hs-888-T (ATCC).

name: U-343-MGa
comments: U-343-MG and U-343-MGa were both derived from the same patient biopsy (PMID: 3497714). GOS-3 is a derivative of the human glioblastoma cell line U-343-MG. (DSMZ).

name: HeLaSF
comments:
HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

name: EFM-192B
comments: EFM-192B and EFM-192C were established from the same patient as EFM-192A (DSMZ).

name: H9
comments: The H9 cell line is a clonal derivative of the Hut 78 cell line (ATCC & PMID: 2567177).

name: KPL-1
comments: KPL-1 has been shown by DNA fingerprinting to be cross-contaminated with cell line MCF-7 (DSMZ).

name: COLO-197
comments:
COLO-201, COLO-205 and COLO-206F were all established from the ascites fluid of a patient with adenocarcinoma of the colon.
COLO-197 is a lymphoid line established from the original biopsy of the same patient.
COLO-200 is a lymphoid line establisted from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 565251).

name: RF-48
comments: Misidentified, now shown to be a B-cell lymphoma and not from a gastric cancer (PMID: 12226758). RF-1 and RF-48 were derived from the same patient (PMID: 12226758)

name: OPM-2
comments: OPM-1 and OPM-2 were established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 3926660).

name: UACC-62_CJ1
comments: UACC-62_CJ1 is a resistant sub-clone of UACC-62.

name: LS1034
comments: LS1034-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LS1034.

name: BeWo
comments:
Hs-630-T has been shown to be a derivative of BeWo (PMID: 25877200, Cellosaurus).
JEG-3 has the same DNA profile as BeWo; it was established by serial cloning of BeWo (ECACC & PMID: 4299001).

name: B240
comments: B239 and B240 are matched normal lines initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of cells from the same blood sample as the tumour line NALM-19. (PMID: 1664237)

name: NCI-H2347
comments: NCI-BL2347 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2347 (ATCC).

name: WM983A
comments: WM983A & WM983B were both derived from the same patient. WM983A was derived from the original tumour and WM983B was derived from a metastatic site. (Rockland)

name: OMM2-3
comments: OMM2-5, OMM2-3 and Mel-270 are derived from the same patient (PMID: 28018010).

name: OC-316
comments: OC-314, OC-315 and OC-316 share common ancestry (PMID: 15677628). Sanger and Broad Institute genomic data supports this conclusion for OC-314 & OC-316 (no data has been generated for OC-315).

name: SW620
comments:
SW480 was derived from the primary adenocarcinoma of the colon.
SW620 was derived the following year from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient (ATCC).

name: NCI-H125
comments: NCI-H125 and NCI-H513 have been show to be cross contaminated (ATCC, ICLAC)

name: HCC1395-BL
comments: HCC1395-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as the breast carcinoma cell line HCC1395 (ATCC).

name: LB373-MEL-D
comments: LB373-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB373-MEL, the parental line of LB373-MEL-D.

name: TE-7
comments: TE-2, TE-3, TE-7, TE-12 & TE-13 share common ancestry (PMID: 17804709)

name: MONO-MAC-6
comments: MONO-MAC-1 and MONO-MAC-6 are simultaneous sister cell lines derived from a peripheral blood sample from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: KMS-12-PE
comments: KMS-12-PE and KMS-12-BM were both derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: NCI-BL1819
comments: NCI-H1819 and the matched normal line NCI-BL1819 were derived from the same patient as NCI-H1693 following chemotherapy. (PMID: 8806092)

name: OVCAR-5
comments: Suspected mis-identification. Originally thought to be a high grade ovarian serous adenocarcinoma but suspected to have a upper gastrointestinal origin (DOI: 10.1093/nar/gkw578).

name: MCC14-2
comments: MCC14-1 & MCC14-2 were both established from the same nodal metastasis. (PMID: 7814141).

name: Hs-791-T
comments: Hs-870-T, Hs-860-T and Hs-791-T were derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus, ATCC)

name: KMS-12-BM
comments: KMS-12-PE and KMS-12-BM were both derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: SCLC-21H
comments: SCLC-21H & SCLC-22H were derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: J-RT3-T3-5
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: CII
comments: Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) immortalized. CI formerly thought of as a B-lymphoblastoid sister of CII is now deemed a subclone of CII. (DSMZ)

name: HCC-827
comments: HCC-827-GR5 is a Gefitinib resistant clone of HCC-827. (10.1126/science.1141478).

name: A2780ADR
comments:
A2780cis is a cisplatin resistant subclone of A2780.
A2780ADR is an adriamycin resistant subclone of A2780 (ECACC).

name: MZ1-B
comments: MZ1-B is a transformed lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as MZ1-PC (Cellosaurus).

name: J82-EBV
comments: https://www.nature.com/articles/301429a0.pdf J82-EBV was derived from the same patient as J82.

name: NTERA-2-cl-D1
comments:
NTERA-2 was established in 1980 from a nude mouse xenograft of the Tera 2 cell line. 
NTERA-2-cl-D1 is a sub-clone of NTERA-2 (ATCC).

name: Hs-934-T
comments: Hs-934-T and HS-935-T were both derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus).

name: NCI-BL2347
comments: NCI-BL2347 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2347 (ATCC).

name: NCI-BL2087
comments: NCI-BL2087 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2087 (ATCC).

name: EM-3
comments:
EM-2 and EM-3 were derived from the same patient.
EM-2 was established +28 days after bone marrow transplantation.
EM-3 was established +47 days  after bone marrow transplantation (DSMZ).

name: SNU-C2B
comments: SNU-C2A and SNU-C2B were both derived from the same nude mouse xenograft. SNU-C2A was derived at the third passage while SNU-C2B was derived at the fourth passage (ATCC).

name: Hs-888-Lu
comments: Hs-888-Lu and Hs-888-Sk were derived using normal tissue from the same patient as the metastatically derived tumour cell line Hs-888-T (ATCC).

name: GR-ST
comments:
ST is a subclone of Tanoue.
GR-ST is a subclone of ST cells transformed with human G-CSF receptor cDNA (JCRB).

name: U-118-MG
comments:
U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC). 
1321N1 is a subclone of 1181N1 which itself is a subclone of U-118 MG  (ECACC).

name: RH-3
comments: RH-28 and RH-3 were both derived from the same tumour. (PMID: 9530337).

name: MEC-1
comments: MEC-1 and MEC-2 were both established from the same patient (PMID: 10071128).

name: EM-2
comments:
EM-2 and EM-3 were derived from the same patient.
EM-2 was established +28 days after bone marrow transplantation.
EM-3 was established +47 days  after bone marrow transplantation (DSMZ).

name: M059J
comments: M059K and M059J cells concurrently from the same tumor specimen from a 33 year old male patient with untreated glioblastoma (ATCC).

name: GP5d
comments: GP5d has been established from the same adenocarcinoma as GP2d (ECACC).

name: U-HO1
comments: U-HO1-PTPN1 was derived from U-HO1 by stable transfection with non-receptor protein-tyrosine phosphatase N1 (PTPN1) (DOI: 10.1186/1471-2121-11-99).

name: COLO-685
comments: COLO-685 was established from the same patient as COLO-684 (DSMZ).

name: SK-BR-3
comments: AU565 and SK-BR-3 were derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: ETK-1
comments: ETK-1 has been shown by STR profiling to be contaminated with SSP-25 (ICLAC)

name: SH-SY5Y
comments: SH-SY5Y is a thrice cloned (SK-N-SH -> SH-SY -> SH-SY5 -> SH-SY5Y) subline of the neuroblastoma cell line SK-N-SH (ATCC).

name: KP-3N
comments:
KP-3L cells were established using tumor nodules removed from the liver of mouse that had KP-3 cells injected into the spleen (JCRB).
KP-3N was derived from parent line KP-3 (PMID: 2172194).

name: Hs-294-T
comments: Hs-294-T and A101D were isolated from the same donor tissue (ATCC).

name: SEM-K2
comments: SEM-K2 is subclone of the SEM cell line (DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2141.1995.tb05207.x)

name: NCI-BL1437
comments: NCI-BL1437 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1437. (ATCC)

name: MZ7-mel
comments: MZ7-B and MZ7-mel are derived from the same patient (DOI: 10.1073/pnas.0500090102).

name: UACC-62
comments: UACC-62_CJ1 is a resistant sub-clone of UACC-62.

name: 21PT
comments:
21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).

name: TGBC2TKB
comments: TGBC1TKB & TGBC2TKB are from the same patient (RIKEN).

name: MDA-PCa-2a
comments: MDA-PCa-2a and MDA-PCa-2b were derived from samples taken from different areas of the same tumour resection. (PMID: 9815652)

name: KP-1N
comments:
KP-1N has been shown to be a derivative of PANC-1. 
KP-1NL is a subline of KP-1N (ICLAC).

name: MC-IXC
comments: MC-IXC is a twice cloned subline of the neuroepithelioma cell line SK-N-MC (ATCC).

name: HCT-8
comments: DLD-1, HCT-15, HCT-8 and HRT-18 have been shown to have a common genetic origin (ECACC & PMID: 9809040).

name: Ishikawa(Heraklio)02ER-
comments: Ishikawa and Ishikawa(Heraklio)02ER- were derived from the same patient.

name: RWPE2-W99
comments:
RWPE-2 was derived from RWPE-1 by transformation with Ki-ras using the Kirsten murine sarcoma virus.
RWPE2-W99 cell line was derived from the RWPE-2 by cloning in soft agar to select cells that show high expression of Ki-ras (ATCC). 
WPE1-NA22 cells were derived from RWPE-1 cells by exposure to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (ATCC).

name: LB996-EBV
comments: LB996-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB996-RCC.

name: MM1R
comments:
MM1R is a dexamethasone resistant line derived from MM1. 
MM1S is a dexamethasone sensitive line derived from MM1 (ATCC).

name: MOLM-14
comments: MOLM-13 and MOLM-14 are sister cell lines, both established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (DSMZ).

name: Onda-9
comments:
Onda-9R was established from a recurrence of a glioblastoma which had previously been sampled and used to derive Onda-9. 
Onda-9R-B12 is a clonal cell line derived from Onda-9R (JCRB).

name: J82
comments: J82-EBV was derived from the same patient as J82.

name: RT112-84
comments: RT112-84 and RT-112 share common ancestry (DSMZ, ECACC).

name: HuTu-80
comments: AZ-521 was originally reported as a human gastric cancer cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of AZ-521 is identical to the HuTu-80 cell line which was derived from a human duodenum carcinoma (JCRB).

name: LN-992
comments: LN-319 was found to be a derivative of LN-992. (PubMed=22570425).

name: PEO4
comments:
PEO1 is from the same patient as the PEO4 and PEO6.

PEO4 was collected after clinical resistance developed to chemotherapy.
PEO6 was collected at advanced, terminal stage disease. (ECACC)

name: YSCCC-G100
comments: Resistant to 100nM of gemcitabine (DOI: 10.1007/s00534-011-0376-7). YSCCC-G10 and YSCCC-G100 are gemcitabine‐resistant cells generated by exposing the YSCCC cell line to 10nM and 100nM of gemcitabine respectively (DOI: 10.1007/s00534-011-0376-7).

name: HT-1080
comments:
HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).

name: NCI-BL1184
comments: NCI-BL1184 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1184. (ATCC)

name: NAMALWA-PNT
comments:
MUTZ-1 has been shown to be  derivative of NAMALWA (PMID: 19344951)
NAMALWA-PNT is a subline of NAMALWA which shows differential expression of immunoglobulin and MYC genes and of some cell surface antigens (DSMZ).

name: RPK-1
comments:
KLM-1 and RPK-1 were both derived from the PK-1 cell line. 
KLM-1 was generated through injection of PK-1 and tumour formation in nude mice. (RIKEN, PMID: 8872523).
RPK-1 is a gemcitabine resistant sublcone of PK-1. (PMID: 22490663)

name: GOS-3
comments: U-343-MG and U-343-MGa were both derived from the same patient biopsy (PMID: 3497714). GOS-3 is a derivative of the human glioblastoma cell line U-343-MG. (DSMZ).

name: DERL-2
comments: DERL-2 and DERL-7 are derived from the same patient. (DSMZ).

name: FTC-133
comments: FTC-133, FTC-236 and FTC-238 were all derived from the same individual (ECACC).

name: U-138-MG
comments:
U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC). 
1321N1 is a subclone of 1181N1 which itself is a subclone of U-118 MG  (ECACC).

name: PEO1
comments:
PEO1 is from the same patient as the PEO4 and PEO6.

PEO4 was collected after clinical resistance developed to chemotherapy.
PEO6 was collected at advanced, terminal stage disease. (ECACC)

name: Hs-630-T
comments:
Hs-630-T has been shown to be a derivative of BeWo (PMID: 25877200, Cellosaurus).
JEG-3 has the same DNA profile as BeWo; it was established by serial cloning of BeWo (ECACC & PMID: 4299001).

name: YSCCC
comments: YSCCC-G10 and YSCCC-G100 are gemcitabine‐resistant cells generated by exposing the YSCCC cell line to 10nM and 100nM of gemcitabine respectively (DOI: 10.1007/s00534-011-0376-7).

name: MOLT-17
comments: MOLT-16 and MOLT-17  are sister cell lines both established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (DSMZ).

name: HCC38-BL
comments: HCC38-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC38 (ATCC).

name: COLO-205
comments:
COLO-201, COLO-205 and COLO-206F were all established from the ascites fluid of a patient with adenocarcinoma of the colon.
COLO-197 is a lymphoid line established from the original biopsy of the same patient.
COLO-200 is a lymphoid line establisted from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 565251).

name: SK-N-BE-2
comments:
BE2-M17 is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2.
BE2-C is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2 (ATCC).

name: Mac-2B
comments:
MAC-1, MAC-2A & MAC-2B were all derived from the same patient. (10.1056/NEJM199204233261704).
Mac-1 was derived in 1985 from circulating Sézary-like cells in the peripheral blood.
Mac-2A and Mac-2B were started from separate skin-tumor nodules in 1987.

name: Hey-A8
comments: Hey-A8 and Hey-C2, are Cisplatin resistant derivations of HEY generated in athymic nude mice (PMID: 23934194).

name: NCI-H2073
comments: NCI-H1993 and NCI-H2073 were derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: MUTZ-7
comments: MUTZ-6 and MUTZ-7 were derived independently, but from the same original peripheral blood cell sample as MUTZ-5. (PMID: 11516110)

name: HCC1937-BL
comments: HCC1937-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1937 (ATCC).

name: MUTZ-5
comments: MUTZ-6 and MUTZ-7 were derived independently, but from the same original peripheral blood cell sample as MUTZ-5. (PMID: 11516110)

name: 22RV1
comments: Cell line was derived from a human prostate carcinoma xenograft (CWR22R) that was serially propagated in nude mice after castration-induced regression and relapse of the parental, androgen-dependent CWR22 xenograft (DSMZ).

name: SK-N-MC
comments: MC-IXC is a twice cloned subline of the neuroepithelioma cell line SK-N-MC (ATCC).

name: MKN28
comments: MKN28 has been shown to be a derivitive of MKN74 (JCRB & ICLAC).

name: IGR-39
comments:
IGR-37 and IGR-39 derived from the same patient.
IGR-37 was established from a lymph node metastasis.
IGR-39 was established from a primary (achromic) cutaneous tumor (DSMZ).

name: Hs-895-Sk
comments: Hs-895-Sk is a normal cell line derived from the same patient as Hs-895-T (ATCC).

name: PANC-10-05
comments: Panc-10-05 was derived from the same patient as the PL45 cell line (ATCC).

name: HuNS1
comments: Potentially mis-identified: Grand-parent cell line (GM01500) was originally thought to be a myeloma cell line but is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line. (Cellosaurus)

name: HCM-SANG-0311-C15-B
comments:
HCM-SANG-0311-C15-B was derived from a sample obtained prior to the patient receiving chemotherapy.
HCM-SANG-0311-C15 is derived from a sample collected following chemotherapy (Capecitabine & Dexamethasone).

name: RMZ-RC2
comments: RMZ-RC2 and RMZ-RC5 are clonal cell lines derived from RMZ (DOI: 10.1038/bjc.1986.273).

name: A2780cis
comments:
A2780cis is a cisplatin resistant subclone of A2780.
A2780ADR is an adriamycin resistant subclone of A2780 (ECACC).

name: NCI-H209
comments: NCI-BL209 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H209 (ATCC).

name: 93T449
comments: 94T778 was established from the second recurrence of the tumor from the same patient from which the 93T449 cell line was derived (ATCC).

name: MM1S
comments:
MM1R is a dexamethasone resistant line derived from MM1. 
MM1S is a dexamethasone sensitive line derived from MM1 (ATCC).

name: WM-239A
comments:
WM115, WM266-4, WM239A and WM165-1 were all derived from the same patient. 
WM115 cell line originated from the primary tumor, and WM239A, WM165-1 and WM266-4 were from individual lymph-node metastases (Rockland).

name: LB771-PBL
comments: LB771-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB771-HNC.

name: LB647-SCLC
comments: LB647-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB647-SCLC.

name: HEL-92-1-7
comments: HEL and HEL-92-1-7 share common ancestry (PMID: 25877200).

name: NCI-ADR-RES
comments: NCI-ADR-RES has been shown to be derivitive of OVCAR-8 (ICLAC)

name: RCC4-VHL
comments:
RCC4-VHL was established from RCC4 by stable transfection with the vector, pcDNA3-VHL, conferring neomycin resistance and encoding the von Hippel-Lindau (VHL) tumour suppressor gene product pVHL (ECACC). RCC4-emptyvector and RCC4-VHL were derived from the RCC4 cell line by stable transfection with pcDNA3 and pCDNA3-VHL respectively (ECACC). 
SLR24 was shown to be a RCC4 derivative (ICLAC).

name: MZ7-B
comments: MZ7-B and MZ7-mel are derived from the same patient (DOI: 10.1073/pnas.0500090102).

name: Ramos
comments: Ramos-2G6-4C10 was derived from the Ramos cell line by repetitive cloning with selection for low constitutive expression of CD23 and maximum stimulation of CD23 expression by IL4 (ATCC).

name: KCI-MOH1
comments: KCI-MOH1 is a derivative of HPAC (ICLAC).

name: GA-10-Clone-4
comments: GA-10-Clone-4 and GA-10-Clone-20 are subclones of the GA 10 cell line derived by culturing the parental line on semi solid medium conditioned by a feeder layer (ATCC).

name: PA-TU-8988S
comments: PA-TU-8988T and PA-TU-8988S are sister cell lines established from the same patient (DSMZ, PMID:1348891).

name: MCF7
comments: KPL-1 has been shown by DNA fingerprinting to be cross-contaminated with cell line MCF-7 (DSMZ).

name: SSP-25
comments: ETK-1 has been shown by STR profiling to be contaminated with SSP-25 (ICLAC)

name: SKG-II
comments:
SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: CMK11-5
comments:
CMK11-5 is a subclone of CMK (PMID: 1391807).
CMK, CMK-86 and CMK-11-5 share high SNP identity (DOI: 10.1038/nature11003).

name: HL-60
comments: PLB-985 is known to be cross contaminated with HL-60 (ICLAC).

name: Raji
comments:
TDL-4 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji (ICLAC).
NC-37 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji by DNA fingerptrinting (ATCC).

name: SW579
comments: CGTH-W-1 is a subclone of SW-579 established in 1995 (PMID: 25877200).

name: NCI-H1304
comments: NCI-H1870 and NCI-H1304 are known syonymous lines (ICLAC).

name: GR-M
comments: GR-M has been shown to be cross-contaminated with PSN1 (DOI: 10.1038/nature14397).

name: ACN
comments: LN-464 and ACN share common ancestry (Sanger & Broad).

name: NCI-BL128
comments: NCI-BL128 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H128. (ATCC)

name: SK-NEP-1
comments: Expression profile suggests origin is Ewings Sarcoma (DOI: 10.1002/pbc.21099).

name: COLO-699N
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: Mero-84
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: GT3TKB
comments: GT3TKB has been shown to be cross contaminated with cell line RERF-LC-AI (PMID: 16643607).

name: HuT-78
comments: The H9 cell line is a clonal derivative of the Hut 78 cell line (ATCC & PMID: 2567177).

name: M059K
comments: M059K and M059J cells concurrently from the same tumor specimen from a 33 year old male patient with untreated glioblastoma (ATCC).

name: U-937
comments: TUR (TPA U937 Resistant) is a stably transfected cell line generated by Ralf Hass and Masanori Hirano in 1992 from U-937 (ATCC).

name: HCM-SANG-0311-C15
comments:
HCM-SANG-0311-C15-B was derived from a sample obtained prior to the patient receiving chemotherapy.
HCM-SANG-0311-C15 is derived from a sample collected following chemotherapy (Capecitabine & Dexamethasone).

name: CHLA-10
comments: CHLA-9 and CHLA-10 were derived from the same patient. (10.1158/0008-5472.CAN-04-0377).

name: Mero-25
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: OCI-Ly13-1
comments:
OCI-Ly13-1 and OCI-Ly13-2 were derived from the same patient. 
OCI-Ly13-1 was established from a sample taken at diagnosis whereas OCI-Ly13-2 was established from a sample obtained during relapse (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V69.5.1307.1307).

name: HLF
comments: HLE and HLF were derived from the same patient (PMID: 52570).

name: SBC-2
comments: SBC-1 and SBC-2 exhibit the same DNA profile (JCRB).

name: LB373-MEL
comments: LB373-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB373-MEL, the parental line of LB373-MEL-D.

name: Mero-48d
comments: Mero-48a (Pleural Cavity), Mero-48b (Omentum), Mero-48c (Liver) and Mero-48d (Pericardium) are derived from 4 solid tumours taken from the same patient (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.2910440212).

name: HTK-
comments:
HOS and 143B originated from the same patient: 143B is TK- and originated indirectly from HOS which is TK+ (ECACC & PMID: 20544518). 
HTK- and 143B have a common STR profile and are thought to be the same cell line (ECACC).

name: CHLA-15
comments: CHLA-15 and CHLA-20 are derived from the same patient. (https://www.cccells.org/dl/NB_Data_Sheets/CHLA-20_Cell_Line_Data_Sheet_COGcell_org.pdf).

name: ARH-77
comments: ARH-77 is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line (PMID: 12592342).

name: LN-464
comments: LN-464 and ACN share common ancestry (Sanger & Broad).

name: TGBC1TKB
comments: TGBC1TKB & TGBC2TKB are from the same patient (RIKEN).

name: NCI-H2087
comments: NCI-BL2087 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2087 (ATCC).

name: LU-99
comments: LU-99A is a subclone of LU-99.

name: Malme-3M
comments: Malme-3M is a tumour line isolated from the same patient as Malme-3, a normal skin fibroblast (ATCC).

name: CHLA-9
comments: CHLA-9 and CHLA-10 were derived from the same patient. (10.1158/0008-5472.CAN-04-0377).

name: YSCCC-G10
comments: Resistant to 10nM of gemcitabine (DOI: 10.1007/s00534-011-0376-7). YSCCC-G10 and YSCCC-G100 are gemcitabine‐resistant cells generated by exposing the YSCCC cell line to 10nM and 100nM of gemcitabine respectively (DOI: 10.1007/s00534-011-0376-7).

name: Hey-C2
comments: Hey-A8 and Hey-C2, are Cisplatin resistant derivations of HEY generated in athymic nude mice (PMID: 23934194).

name: WM-165-1
comments:
WM115, WM266-4, WM239A and WM165-1 were all derived from the same patient. 
WM115 cell line originated from the primary tumor, and WM239A, WM165-1 and WM266-4 were from individual lymph-node metastases (Rockland).

name: BE2-C
comments:
BE2-M17 is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2.
BE2-C is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2 (ATCC).

name: LS-180
comments: LS-180 is a variant of LS-174T that has not been trypsinized during subculture, however LS-174T has been subcultured by trypsinization (ATCC).

name: A2780
comments:
A2780cis is a cisplatin resistant subclone of A2780.
A2780ADR is an adriamycin resistant subclone of A2780 (ECACC).

name: PEO6
comments:
PEO1 is from the same patient as the PEO4 and PEO6.

PEO4 was collected after clinical resistance developed to chemotherapy.
PEO6 was collected at advanced, terminal stage disease. (ECACC)

name: PLB-985
comments: PLB-985 is known to be cross contaminated with HL-60 (ICLAC).

name: ST
comments:
ST is a subclone of Tanoue.
GR-ST is a subclone of ST cells transformed with human G-CSF receptor cDNA (JCRB).

name: 21MT-1
comments:
21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).

name: NK-92
comments: NK-92MI is an interleukin 2 independent Natural Killer Cell line derived from the NK-92 by transfection (ATCC).

name: MONO-MAC-1
comments: MONO-MAC-1 and MONO-MAC-6 are simultaneous sister cell lines derived from a peripheral blood sample from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: 253JB-V
comments: 253JB-V was derived from 253J following implantion into the muscular wall of the bladder of athymic nude mice. (10.1016/S0022-5347(01)66923-4).

name: ME-180
comments: SF767 has been shown to be a derivative of ME-180 (PMID: 22570425).

name: SKG-I
comments: The SKG-I-TS cell line was derived from SKG-I by transfection with a thymidylate synthase (TS)-expressing vector (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.11221).

name: B2-17
comments:
B2-17 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251.
SNB19 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251 (ICLAC).

name: 1205Lu
comments: 1205Lu was dervied by serial passaging of WM793 through immune deficient mice and harvesting lung metastases (DOI: 10.4172/1948-5956.1000401).

name: PK-45P
comments: PK-45H and PK-45P were both derived from the same patient. (RIKEN).

name: NALM-19
comments: B239 and B240 are matched normal lines initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of cells from the same blood sample as the tumour line NALM-19. (PMID: 1664237)

name: LB2518-EBV
comments: LB2518-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB2518-MEL.

name: SNU-C2A
comments: SNU-C2A and SNU-C2B were both derived from the same nude mouse xenograft. SNU-C2A was derived at the third passage while SNU-C2B was derived at the fourth passage (ATCC).

name: SKG-IIB
comments:
Model reference: https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: PSN1
comments: GR-M has been shown to be cross-contaminated with PSN1 (DOI: 10.1038/nature14397).

name: L3-3
comments: Derived through sequential passaging in nude mice of cell line COLO-357. The L3-3 cell line is one of multiple lines established by sequential passages of a human pancreatic cancer cell line COLO-357 through the nude mouse liver. (PMID: 1544114)

name: LB996-RCC
comments: LB996-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB996-RCC.

name: HuH-6
comments: HUH-6-clone5 is a subclone of HuH-6 (PMID: 57894).

name: BE-13
comments: BE-13 and PEER show identical DNA fingerprints presumably due to cross-contamination; however, their diploid and tetraploid karyotypes are indicative of earlier and later passage numbers suggesting that BE-13 is derived from PEER, rather than vice-versa (DSMZ).

name: HCC1143-BL
comments: HCC1143-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated using peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1143 (ATCC).

name: MDA-PCa-2b
comments: MDA-PCa-2a and MDA-PCa-2b were derived from samples taken from different areas of the same tumour resection. (PMID: 9815652)

name: LS1034-PBL
comments: LS1034-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LS1034.

name: NCI-BL209
comments: NCI-BL209 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H209 (ATCC).

name: YMB-1-E
comments: YMB-1 and YMB-1-E have been shown to be derivatives of ZR-75-1 (JCRB, ICLAC, PMID: 23136038).

name: BB30-HNC
comments: BB30-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB30-HNC.

name: Jurkat-Clone-E6-1
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: B239
comments: B239 and B240 are matched normal lines initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of cells from the same blood sample as the tumour line NALM-19. (PMID: 1664237)

name: HT-29
comments: WiDr has been shown to be a derivitive of HT-29 (ICLAC).

name: LoVo
comments: NCOL-1 has been shown to be derived from LoVo (ICLAC).

name: HCC38
comments: HCC38-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC38 (ATCC).

name: TUR
comments: TUR (TPA U937 Resistant) is a stably transfected cell line generated by Ralf Hass and Masanori Hirano in 1992 from U-937 (ATCC).

name: MOLT-3
comments: MOLT-4 was derived from the same patient as MOLT-3 (ATCC).

name: COR-L23
comments: COR-L23-R is a multi-drug resistant sub-line derived from the parent line COR-L23 after treatment with doxorubicin (ECACC).

name: HEp-2
comments:
HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

name: PK-1
comments:
KLM-1 and RPK-1 were both derived from the PK-1 cell line. 
KLM-1 was generated through injection of PK-1 and tumour formation in nude mice. (RIKEN, PMID: 8872523).
RPK-1 is a gemcitabine resistant sublcone of PK-1. (PMID: 22490663)

name: CMK
comments:
CMK11-5 is a subclone of CMK (PMID: 1391807).
CMK, CMK-86 and CMK-11-5 share high SNP identity (DOI: 10.1038/nature11003).

name: PEER
comments: BE-13 and PEER show identical DNA fingerprints presumably due to cross-contamination; however, their diploid and tetraploid karyotypes are indicative of earlier and later passage numbers suggesting that BE-13 is derived from PEER, rather than vice-versa (DSMZ).

name: Hey
comments: Hey-A8 and Hey-C2, are Cisplatin resistant derivations of HEY generated in athymic nude mice (PMID: 23934194).

name: Hs-935-T
comments: Hs-934-T and HS-935-T were both derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus).

name: HCC2218-BL
comments: HCC2218-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC2218 (ATCC).

name: VP229
comments: VP229 was derived from a breast cancer biopsy obtained from the primary tumour, VP267 was derived 14 months later from a local recurrence of the tumour (ECACC).

name: RPMI-7932
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: KP-3L
comments:
KP-3L cells were established using tumor nodules removed from the liver of mouse that had KP-3 cells injected into the spleen (JCRB).
KP-3N was derived from parent line KP-3 (PMID: 2172194).

name: C2BBe1
comments: The C2BBe1 (brush border expressing) cell line was cloned in 1988 from the Caco 2 cell line (ATCC).

name: PGA-1
comments: PG-B95-8 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as PGA-1 (DSMZ).

name: HCC1187-BL
comments: HCC1187-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1187 (ATCC).

name: Mero-83
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: NCI-H128
comments: NCI-BL128 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H128. (ATCC)

name: PK-45H
comments: PK-45H and PK-45P were both derived from the same patient. (RIKEN).

name: NCI-H1819
comments: NCI-H1819 and the matched normal line NCI-BL1819 were derived from the same patient as NCI-H1693 following chemotherapy. (PMID: 8806092)

name: OC-314
comments: OC-314, OC-315 and OC-316 share common ancestry (PMID: 15677628). Sanger and Broad Institute genomic data supports this conclusion for OC-314 & OC-316 (no data has been generated for OC-315).

name: COLO-206F
comments:
COLO-201, COLO-205 and COLO-206F were all established from the ascites fluid of a patient with adenocarcinoma of the colon.
COLO-197 is a lymphoid line established from the original biopsy of the same patient.
COLO-200 is a lymphoid line establisted from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 565251).

name: WM983B
comments: WM983A & WM983B were both derived from the same patient. WM983A was derived from the original tumour and WM983B was derived from a metastatic site. (Rockland)

name: COLO-320-HSR
comments: COLO-320 and COLO-320-HSR share common ancestry.

name: MOLT-16
comments: MOLT-16 and MOLT-17  are sister cell lines both established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (DSMZ).

name: LC-1-sq
comments:
LC-1F (Floating variant) is from the same patient as LC-1-sq (Lung Cancer-1/Squamous). 
LC-1-sq-SF is a variant of LC-1-sq cultured in serum-free media (RIKEN).

name: NCI-BL2077
comments: NCI-BL2077 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H2077. (PMID: 8806092)

name: AGR-ON
comments:
CEM/C1 is a camptothecin resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
CEM/C2 is a multi drug resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
AGR-ON is a derivative of CEM-AG, itself a derivative of CCRF-CEM, selected for ability to produce CSF (ATCC).

name: SCC90
comments: SCC152 was established from a recurrence of a squamous cell carcinoma which had been used to derive SCC90 (ATCC).

name: Malme-3
comments: Malme-3M is a tumour line isolated from the same patient as Malme-3, a normal skin fibroblast (ATCC).

name: LB2518-MEL
comments: LB2518-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB2518-MEL.

name: WM-115
comments:
WM115, WM266-4, WM239A and WM165-1 were all derived from the same patient. 
WM115 cell line originated from the primary tumor, and WM239A, WM165-1 and WM266-4 were from individual lymph-node metastases (Rockland).

name: Mero-48a
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC). Mero-48a (Pleural Cavity), Mero-48b (Omentum), Mero-48c (Liver) and Mero-48d (Pericardium) are derived from 4 solid tumours taken from the same patient (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.2910440212).

name: MUTZ-6
comments: MUTZ-6 and MUTZ-7 were derived independently, but from the same original peripheral blood cell sample as MUTZ-5. (PMID: 11516110)

name: RBE
comments: RBE and SSP-25 were originally reported to have been derived from the same patient. However, their STR profiles indicate that these cell lines come from different individuals (RIKEN).

name: UT-7
comments:
UT-7-EPO is an erythropoietin-dependent subline of UT-7 (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V82.2.456.456). 
UT-7-GM is a subline of UT-7 and is a bipotential cell line that can be induced to differentiate into erythroid and megakaryocytic lineages by EPO and TPO (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V89.11.4021). 
UT-7-TPO is a thrombopoietin-dependent subline of UT-7-GM (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V87.11.4552.bloodjournal87114552).

name: COV413B
comments: COV413A and COV413B are derived from the same patient. (ECACC).

name: U-343-MG
comments: U-343-MG and U-343-MGa were both derived from the same patient biopsy (PMID: 3497714). GOS-3 is a derivative of the human glioblastoma cell line U-343-MG. (DSMZ).

name: SLR24
comments:
RCC4-emptyvector and RCC4-VHL were derived from the RCC4 cell line by stable transfection with pcDNA3 and pCDNA3-VHL respectively (ECACC). 
SLR24 was shown to be a RCC4 derivative (ICLAC).

name: NC-37
comments:
TDL-4 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji (ICLAC).
NC-37 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji by DNA fingerptrinting (ATCC).

name: COLO-699
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: COLO-818
comments:
COLO-818 has been shown to come from the same patient as COLO-800 (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.25242.)
COLO-800 and COLO-794 were both derived from the same patient (ECACC).

name: WM-164
comments: 451Lu is a selected xenograft aggressive metastatic sub-line of WM164 (Rockland).

name: RWPE-2
comments:
RWPE-2 was derived from RWPE-1 by transformation with Ki-ras using the Kirsten murine sarcoma virus.
RWPE2-W99 cell line was derived from the RWPE-2 by cloning in soft agar to select cells that show high expression of Ki-ras (ATCC). 
WPE1-NA22 cells were derived from RWPE-1 cells by exposure to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (ATCC).

name: RERF-LC-MA
comments: RERF-LC-MA has the same DNA profile as lung squamous carcinoma cell line SK-MES-1 (JCRB).

name: F-36E
comments: F-36P is the parent of F-36E.  F-36P has been cultured with granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) or interleukin-3 (IL-3) while F-36E can be maintained in the presence of erythropoietin only. (PubMed=1834251).

name: LB1047-EBV
comments: LB1047-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB1047-RCC.

name: LN-Z308
comments: LNZTA3WT4 was derived from the glioblastoma cell line LN-Z308 (ATCC).

name: RH-41
comments: RH-41 and RH-4 were both derived from the same patient sample. (PMID: 23882450)

name: LB2241-RCC
comments: LB2241-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB2241-RCC.

name: VP267
comments: VP229 was derived from a breast cancer biopsy obtained from the primary tumour, VP267 was derived 14 months later from a local recurrence of the tumour (ECACC).

name: COV413A
comments: COV413A and COV413B are derived from the same patient. (ECACC).

name: RERF-LC-AI
comments: GT3TKB has been shown to be cross contaminated with cell line RERF-LC-AI (PMID: 16643607).

name: PaCaDD-183
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: PG-B95-8
comments: PG-B95-8 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as PGA-1 (DSMZ).

name: CEMC2
comments:
CEM/C1 is a camptothecin resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
CEM/C2 is a multi drug resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
AGR-ON is a derivative of CEM-AG, itself a derivative of CCRF-CEM, selected for ability to produce CSF (ATCC).

name: COLO-829
comments:
COLO-829 was derived from a sample taken prior to chemotherapy for metastatic melanoma.
COLO 829BL was established from the same patient by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of a sample of peripheral blood (ATCC).

name: BB65-RCC
comments: BB65-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB65-RCC.

name: HCC2157-BL
comments: HCC2157-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC2157 (ATCC).

name: NCI-H1693
comments: NCI-H1819 and the matched normal line NCI-BL1819 were derived from the same patient as NCI-H1693 following chemotherapy. (PMID: 8806092)

name: WIL2-NS
comments: WIL2-S is a HAT sensitive variant of the WIL2-NS cell line (ATCC).

name: PEO14
comments:
PEO14, PEO23 and TO14 were derived from the same patient. (PMID: 3167863).
PEO14 and PEO23 samples were obtained from ascites, PEO14 prior to therapy and PEO23 following chemotherapy.
TO14 was derived from a solid metastasis in the omentum.

name: RKO
comments: RKO-E6 was generated from the colon carcinoma line RKO by transfection with pCMV E6 using Lipofectin (ATCC).

name: BB30-PBL
comments: BB30-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB30-HNC.

name: M14
comments: MDA-MB-435 and its variant MDA-MB435S have been found to be cross contaminated with M14 (ICLAC, DOI: 10.1002/ijc.31067)

name: KMS-21-BM
comments:
The origin of KMS-21-BM is unclear. 
The line was though to originate from the same patient as KMS-21-PE however STR profiling has showed this to be incorrect. The true donor infomration for both lines is consequently uncertain. (JCRB, ICLAC)

name: COV362
comments: COV362-4 is a subline of an early passage of the cell line COV362. (ECACC).

name: SF8657
comments: SF8657 is a finite cell line of fibroblasts established from a skin biopsy of a non-exposed individual with stomach cancer.

name: LN-443
comments: LN-443 is a subline of LN-444, and accordingly, both lines contain the same PTEN mutation. (PubMed=22570425).

name: COLO-738
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: TMH-1
comments: IHH-4 and TMH-1 share common ancestry having matching STR profiles (JCRB).

name: 94T778
comments: 94T778 was established from the second recurrence of the tumor from the same patient from which the 93T449 cell line was derived (ATCC).

name: NCI-BL2141
comments: NCI-BL2141 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2141 (ATCC).

name: YMB-1
comments: YMB-1 and YMB-1-E have been shown to be derivatives of ZR-75-1 (JCRB, ICLAC, PMID: 23136038).

name: PEA2
comments: PEA1 and PEA2 were both derived from the same patient. PEA1 was obtained prior to therapy, PEA2 was obtained after chemotherapy. (PMID: 3167863)

name: HCC1937
comments: HCC1937-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1937 (ATCC).

name: LB1047-RCC
comments: LB1047-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB1047-RCC.

name: SUM-229PE
comments: SUM229PE was established by Stephen Ethier and distributed by Asterand (later acquired by BioIVT).  ICLAC was notified that the STR profile in Asterand's Certificate of Analysis matched SUM149PT.  Stephen Ethier was contacted to ask about this finding and confirmed that SUM229PE and SUM149PT were established from different donors.  An updated Certificate of Analysis was then issued; looking at the STR profile, the problem appears to have been corrected.  The correct STR profile is available on Cellosaurus. (ICLAC v9)

name: SW626
comments: SW626 may have been derived from an ovarian metastasis of a primary adenocarcinoma of the colon (ATCC).

name: CHL-1
comments:
HCMB and RPMI-7932 were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).
CHL-1 is a dervivative of RPMI-7932 (ATCC).

COLO-699N (COLO-699) and COLO-738 were found to be indistinguishable from RPMI-7932 by STR profiling. All three cell lines were received from the same depositor (ECACC).

name: F-36P
comments: F-36P is the parent of F-36E.  F-36P has been cultured with granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) or interleukin-3 (IL-3) while F-36E can be maintained in the presence of erythropoietin only. (PubMed=1834251).

name: NCI-H1437
comments: NCI-BL1437 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1437. (ATCC)

name: IHH-4
comments: IHH-4 and TMH-1 share common ancestry having matching STR profiles (JCRB).

name: MEC-2
comments: MEC-1 and MEC-2 were both established from the same patient (PMID: 10071128).

name: Hs-888-T
comments: Hs-888-Lu and Hs-888-Sk were derived using normal tissue from the same patient as the metastatically derived tumour cell line Hs-888-T (ATCC).

name: MC-CAR
comments: MC-CAR-Z2 is a derivative of MC-CAR (ATCC).

name: HRT-18
comments: DLD-1, HCT-15, HCT-8 and HRT-18 have been shown to have a common genetic origin (ECACC & PMID: 9809040).

name: HCC1599
comments: HCC1599-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1599 (ATCC).

name: TIG-3S
comments:
TIG-3 and TIG-3S were established from fetal lung and skin samples respectively from the same individual (DOI: 10.34425/zs000693).
TIG-3TD is a TERT-immortalised cell line of TIG-3 (Cellosaurus).

name: HLE
comments: HLE and HLF were derived from the same patient (PMID: 52570).

name: MES-SA
comments:
MES-SA-MX2 is a mitoxantrone resistant derivative of the human uterine sarcoma cell line MES-SA (ATCC).
MES-SADx-5 is a multi drug-resistant subclone of MES-SA (ECACC).

name: CP66-EBV
comments: CP66-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP66-MEL.

name: Marcus
comments:
SK-MG-1 and Marcus share common ancestry (JCRB).

RERF-LC-OK has been shown to be contaminated with Marcus cell line (ICLAC).

name: MES-SA-MX2
comments:
MES-SA-MX2 is a mitoxantrone resistant derivative of the human uterine sarcoma cell line MES-SA (ATCC).
MES-SADx-5 is a multi drug-resistant subclone of MES-SA (ECACC).

name: Hs-445
comments: Originally thought to be a Hodgkin's cell line but is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line (PMID: 12592342, Sanger).

name: JKT-beta-del
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: SBC-1
comments: SBC-1 and SBC-2 exhibit the same DNA profile (JCRB).

name: Mero-48c
comments: Mero-48a (Pleural Cavity), Mero-48b (Omentum), Mero-48c (Liver) and Mero-48d (Pericardium) are derived from 4 solid tumours taken from the same patient (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.2910440212).

name: COLO-320
comments: COLO-320 and COLO-320-HSR share common ancestry.

name: RH-28
comments: The RH-28 cell line was derived from a xenograft of tumor tissue obtained from an axillary node metastasis in a previously untreated 17-year-old male. (PMID: 23882450). RH-28 and RH-3 were both derived from the same tumour. (PMID: 9530337).

name: SCLC-22H
comments: SCLC-21H & SCLC-22H were derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: MY-M12
comments: MY-M12 is the subclone of the MY (JCRB).

name: C-4-I
comments: C-4-I and C-4-II were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: COLO-200
comments:
COLO-201, COLO-205 and COLO-206F were all established from the ascites fluid of a patient with adenocarcinoma of the colon.
COLO-197 is a lymphoid line established from the original biopsy of the same patient.
COLO-200 is a lymphoid line establisted from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 565251).

name: SNU-423
comments: Treated by transcatheter arterial embolization with lipoidol plus doxorubicin.

name: NCI-BL2171
comments: NCI-BL2171 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2171 (ATCC).

name: 253J
comments: 253JB-V was derived from 253J following implantion into the muscular wall of the bladder of athymic nude mice. (10.1016/S0022-5347(01)66923-4).

name: SKG-II-SF
comments:
Adapted for growth in serum free media. SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: LB831-EBV
comments: LB831-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB831-BLC.

name: DERL-7
comments: DERL-2 and DERL-7 are derived from the same patient. (DSMZ).

name: OVSAYO
comments: OVMIU and OVSAYO share common ancestry (JCRB).

name: PEAZ-1
comments:
HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).

name: FTC-236
comments: FTC-133, FTC-236 and FTC-238 were all derived from the same individual (ECACC).

name: NCI-H2052
comments: NCI-BL2052 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2052 (ATCC).

name: KNS-81
comments: KNS-81-FD is derived from KNS-81 (JCRB).

name: COG-AR-359
comments: http://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/68/9_Supplement/3743 COG-AR-359 and COG-AR-382 are derived from the same patient. (http://cancerres.aacrjournals.org/content/68/9_Supplement/3743).

name: HKMUS
comments:
SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: OVMIU
comments: OVMIU and OVSAYO share common ancestry (JCRB).

name: NCI-H1395
comments: NCI-BL1395 is a lymphoblastoid line established from the same patient as NCI-H1395 (ATCC).

name: UT-7-TPO
comments:
UT-7-EPO is an erythropoietin-dependent subline of UT-7 (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V82.2.456.456).
