UT-7-GM is a subline of UT-7 and is a bipotential cell line that can be induced to differentiate into erythroid and megakaryocytic lineages by EPO and TPO (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V89.11.4021). 
UT-7-TPO is a thrombopoietin-dependent subline of UT-7-GM (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V87.11.4552.bloodjournal87114552).

name: CCRF-CEM
comments:
CEM/C1 is a camptothecin resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
CEM/C2 is a multi drug resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
AGR-ON is a derivative of CEM-AG, itself a derivative of CCRF-CEM, selected for ability to produce CSF (ATCC).

name: SF767
comments: SF767 has been shown to be a derivative of ME-180 (PMID: 22570425).

name: PaCaDD-165
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: UPCI-SCC-026
comments: UPCI-SCC-026 was derived following recurrance from the same patient as UPCI-SCC-016 (DOI: 10.1016/j.oraloncology.2007.05.003).

name: C-4-II
comments: C-4-I and C-4-II were both derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: HuG1-PI
comments: A variant of HuG1 producing hybrid type of alkaline phosphatase. HuG1-N and HuG1-PI were derived from the parental line HuG1 (JCRB).

name: SKG-I-TS
comments: The SKG-I-TS cell line was derived from SKG-I by transfection with a thymidylate synthase (TS)-expressing vector (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.11221).

name: HCC1187
comments: HCC1187-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1187 (ATCC).

name: D-458MED
comments: D-425MED and D-458MED are derived from the same patient. (PubMed=1822845).

name: Onda-9R-B12
comments:
Onda-9R was established from a recurrence of a glioblastoma which had previously been sampled and used to derive Onda-9. 
Onda-9R-B12 is a clonal cell line derived from Onda-9R (JCRB).

name: SKG-II-TS
comments:
SKG-IIB was established from the same individual as SKG-II (https://ci.nii.ac.jp/naid/110002117678/en).
The SKG-II-LUC and SKG-II-S cell lines were derived from SKG-II by transfection with LUC or TS-expressing vectors respectively (DOI: 10.1159/000063804). 
SKG-II-SF was established from SKG-II by growth in serum-free media (PMID: 9573483). 
The HKMUS cell line has been shown to be a SKG-II-SF derivative (PMID: 20143388).

name: SNB19
comments:
B2-17 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251.
SNB19 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251 (ICLAC).

name: LB2241-EBV
comments: LB2241-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB2241-RCC.

name: NCI-BL2126
comments: NCI-BL2126 is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as NCI-H2126 (ATCC).

name: TIG-3
comments:
TIG-3 and TIG-3S were established from fetal lung and skin samples respectively from the same individual (DOI: 10.34425/zs000693).
TIG-3TD is a TERT-immortalised cell line of TIG-3 (Cellosaurus).

name: NCI-H1876
comments: NCI-H1876 & NCI-H1882 & NCI-H1881 have been derived from the same same patient. (NCI-Navy Medical Oncology Brance Cell Line Supplement DOI: 10.1002/jcb.240630505)

name: T24
comments: ACCS has been shown to be a derivitive of T24 (PMID: 20143388).

name: SK-MG-1
comments:
SK-MG-1 and Marcus share common ancestry (JCRB).

RERF-LC-OK has been shown to be contaminated with Marcus cell line (ICLAC).

name: NCI-H2009
comments: NCI-BL2009 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2009 (ATCC).

name: Mac-2A
comments:
MAC-1, MAC-2A & MAC-2B were all derived from the same patient. (10.1056/NEJM199204233261704).
Mac-1 was derived in 1985 from circulating Sézary-like cells in the peripheral blood.
Mac-2A and Mac-2B were started from separate skin-tumor nodules in 1987.

name: Mero-82
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: Mero-95
comments: Note made of patient's history of exposure to asbestos (ECACC).

name: MMAc-SF
comments: MMAc-SF is a serum-free medium adapted version of the MMAc cell line (RIKEN).

name: KNS-81-FD
comments: KNS-81-FD is derived from KNS-81 (JCRB).

name: Hs-895-T
comments: Hs-895-Sk is a normal cell line derived from the same patient as Hs-895-T (ATCC).

name: PC-9
comments: PC-14 has been shown to be a derivitive of PC-9 (RIKEN, ECACC).

name: RKO-E6
comments: RKO-E6 was generated from the colon carcinoma line RKO by transfection with pCMV E6 using Lipofectin (ATCC).

name: MES-SA-Dx-5
comments:
MES-SA-MX2 is a mitoxantrone resistant derivative of the human uterine sarcoma cell line MES-SA (ATCC).
MES-SADx-5 is a multi drug-resistant subclone of MES-SA (ECACC).

name: TE-12
comments: TE-2, TE-3, TE-7, TE-12 & TE-13 share common ancestry (PMID: 17804709)

name: KKU-M213
comments: Development of cancer within the patient linked to an infection with Opisthorchis viverrini (DOI: 10.1016/j.ijpara.2010.05.002)

name: IGR-37
comments:
IGR-37 and IGR-39 derived from the same patient.
IGR-37 was established from a lymph node metastasis.
IGR-39 was established from a primary (achromic) cutaneous tumor (DSMZ).

name: Onda-9R
comments:
Onda-9R was established from a recurrence of a glioblastoma which had previously been sampled and used to derive Onda-9. 
Onda-9R-B12 is a clonal cell line derived from Onda-9R (JCRB).

name: PEA1
comments: PEA1 and PEA2 were both derived from the same patient. PEA1 was obtained prior to therapy, PEA2 was obtained after chemotherapy. (PMID: 3167863)

name: HUH-6-clone5
comments: HUH-6-clone5 is a subclone of HuH-6 (PMID: 57894).

name: HEC-1
comments:
HEC-1-A was derived from the same patient as HEC-1 (JCRB).
HEC-1-B is a substrain of HEC-1-A (ATCC).

name: SW480
comments:
SW480 was derived from the primary adenocarcinoma of the colon.
SW620 was derived the following year from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient (ATCC).

name: TO14
comments:
PEO14, PEO23 and TO14 were derived from the same patient. (PMID: 3167863).
PEO14 and PEO23 samples were obtained from ascites, PEO14 prior to therapy and PEO23 following chemotherapy.
TO14 was derived from a solid metastasis in the omentum.

name: NCI-BL2009
comments: NCI-BL2009 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2009 (ATCC).

name: A3
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: Mel-270
comments: OMM2-5, OMM2-3 and Mel-270 are derived from the same patient (PMID: 28018010).

name: LNZTA3WT4
comments: LNZTA3WT4 was derived from the glioblastoma cell line LN-Z308 (ATCC).

name: GP2d
comments: GP5d has been established from the same adenocarcinoma as GP2d (ECACC).

name: A375_CJ3
comments: Dabrafenib and Trametinib resistant subclone of A375. A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.

name: COLO-357
comments: The L3-3 cell line is one of multiple lines established by sequential passages of a human pancreatic cancer cell line COLO-357 through the nude mouse liver. (PMID: 1544114)

name: RPMI-6666
comments: RPMI-6666 was initially thought to have been derived from Hodgkin lymphoma, but is now known to be an EBV-positive B-lymphoblastoid cell line (PMID: 12592342).

name: CHLA-20
comments: CHLA-15 and CHLA-20 are derived from the same patient. (https://www.cccells.org/dl/NB_Data_Sheets/CHLA-20_Cell_Line_Data_Sheet_COGcell_org.pdf).

name: NCI-H2126
comments: NCI-BL2126 is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as NCI-H2126 (ATCC).

name: Hs-870-T
comments: Hs-870-T, Hs-860-T and Hs-791-T were derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus, ATCC)

name: A375
comments: A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.

name: SEM
comments: SEM-K2 is subclone of the SEM cell line (DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2141.1995.tb05207.x)

name: BB49-EBV
comments: BB49-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB49-HNC.

name: CP50-EBV
comments: CP50-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP50-MEL-B.

name: HuG1
comments: HuG1-N and HuG1-PI were derived from the parental line HuG1 (JCRB).

name: LS-174T
comments: LS-180 is a variant of LS-174T that has not been trypsinized during subculture, however LS-174T has been subcultured by trypsinization (ATCC).

name: WIDR
comments: WiDr has been shown to be a derivitive of HT-29 (ICLAC).

name: NAMALWA
comments:
MUTZ-1 has been shown to be  derivative of NAMALWA (PMID: 19344951)
NAMALWA-PNT is a subline of NAMALWA which shows differential expression of immunoglobulin and MYC genes and of some cell surface antigens (DSMZ).

name: M120326_2
comments: M120326_2 and M120327_3 were established from two different samples obtained from different regions of the same tumour.

name: JURL-MK2
comments: JURL-MK1 and JURL-MK2 are sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: SCC152
comments: SCC152 was established from a recurrence of a squamous cell carcinoma which had been used to derive SCC90 (ATCC).

name: HPAC
comments: KCI-MOH1 is a derivative of HPAC (ICLAC).

name: NCI-BL2052
comments: NCI-BL2052 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2052 (ATCC).

name: HP
comments:
HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).

name: MUTZ-1
comments:
MUTZ-1 has been shown to be  derivative of NAMALWA (PMID: 19344951)
NAMALWA-PNT is a subline of NAMALWA which shows differential expression of immunoglobulin and MYC genes and of some cell surface antigens (DSMZ).

name: PaCaDD-161
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: ZR-75-1
comments: YMB-1 and YMB-1-E have been shown to be derivatives of ZR-75-1 (JCRB, ICLAC, PMID: 23136038).

name: PWR-1E
comments: PWR-1-E was single cell clone isolated from cells derived from non-neoplastic adult human prostate cells that were infected with the Ad12-SV40 virus (PMID: 8761420).

name: Caco-2
comments: The C2BBe1 (brush border expressing) cell line was cloned in 1988 from the Caco 2 cell line (ATCC).

name: A101D
comments: Hs-294-T and A101D were isolated from the same donor tissue (ATCC).

name: MOR
comments: MOR/CPR has been developed by growing the parent line, MOR, in increasing concentrations of cisplatin. (ECACC),

name: RWPE-1
comments:
RWPE-2 was derived from RWPE-1 by transformation with Ki-ras using the Kirsten murine sarcoma virus.
RWPE2-W99 cell line was derived from the RWPE-2 by cloning in soft agar to select cells that show high expression of Ki-ras (ATCC). 
WPE1-NA22 cells were derived from RWPE-1 cells by exposure to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (ATCC).

name: MZ1-PC
comments: MZ1-B is a transformed lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as MZ1-PC (Cellosaurus).

name: 21MT-2
comments:
21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).

name: SNG-P
comments: SNG-P and SNG-M were establised from primary and metastatic regions respectively of the same tumour (PMID: 858140).

name: U251
comments:
B2-17 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251.
SNB19 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251 (ICLAC).

name: HEC-1-B
comments:
HEC-1-A was derived from the same patient as HEC-1 (JCRB).
HEC-1-B is a substrain of HEC-1-A (ATCC).

name: CEMC1
comments:
CEM/C1 is a camptothecin resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
CEM/C2 is a multi drug resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
AGR-ON is a derivative of CEM-AG, itself a derivative of CCRF-CEM, selected for ability to produce CSF (ATCC).

name: BB49-HNC
comments: BB49-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB49-HNC.

name: CP66-MEL
comments: CP66-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP66-MEL.

name: RF-1
comments: Misidentified, now shown to be a B-cell lymphoma and not from a gastric cancer (PMID: 12226758). RF-1 and RF-48 were derived from the same patient (PMID: 12226758)

name: M120327_3
comments: M120326_2 and M120327_3 were established from two different samples obtained from different regions of the same tumour.

name: Ishikawa
comments: Ishikawa and Ishikawa(Heraklio)02ER- were derived from the same patient.

name: LC-1F
comments:
LC-1F (Floating variant) is from the same patient as LC-1-sq (Lung Cancer-1/Squamous). 
LC-1-sq-SF is a variant of LC-1-sq cultured in serum-free media (RIKEN).

name: CGTH-W-1
comments: CGTH-W-1 is a subclone of SW-579 established in 1995 (PMID: 25877200).

name: SK-MES-1
comments: RERF-LC-MA has the same DNA profile as lung squamous carcinoma cell line SK-MES-1 (JCRB).

name: MDA-MB-435
comments: MDA-MB-435 and its variant MDA-MB435S have been found to be cross contaminated with M14 (ICLAC, DOI: 10.1002/ijc.31067)

name: ICC10-8
comments: ICC10-6 and ICC10-8 were derived from the same individual (DepMap STR).

name: SNG-M
comments: SNG-P and SNG-M were establised from primary and metastatic regions respectively of the same tumour (PMID: 858140).

name: LAMA-87
comments: LAMA-87 is a subclone of LAMA-84 obtained after subcutaneous transplantation of LAMA-84 cells into estrone-treated nude mice (DSMZ).

name: EB2
comments: SNP and STR profiling by the Sanger and Broad Institute indicate both EB-1 and EB2 share common ancestry.

name: K029
comments: K029AX was derived from parental line K029. (Cellosaurus).

name: NCI-H2171
comments: NCI-BL2171 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2171 (ATCC).

name: Mero-48b
comments: Mero-48a (Pleural Cavity), Mero-48b (Omentum), Mero-48c (Liver) and Mero-48d (Pericardium) are derived from 4 solid tumours taken from the same patient (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.2910440212).

name: LU-134-B
comments: Lines LU-134-A and LU-134-B have been shown to be related (RIKEN).

name: NK-92MI
comments: NK-92MI is an interleukin 2 independent Natural Killer Cell line derived from the NK-92 by transfection (ATCC).

name: JiyoyeP-2003
comments:
P3HR-1 is a clonally derived subline of Jiyoye.
2B8 is a HAT sensitive fusion cell line derived from the P3HR-1 (ATCC).

name: Hs-688B-T
comments: Hs-688A-T was derived from the primary tumour and Hs-688B-T was derived from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient. (ATCC).

name: HCC827-GR5
comments: HCC-827-GR5 is a Gefitinib resistant clone of HCC-827. (10.1126/science.1141478).

name: NCI-H2141
comments: NCI-BL2141 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2141 (ATCC).

name: HK-2
comments: The cells were immortalized by transduction with human papilloma virus 16 (HPV-16) E6/E7 genes (ATCC).

name: TIG-3TD
comments:
Telomerase (TERT) immortalised (Cellosaurus). TIG-3 and TIG-3S were established from fetal lung and skin samples respectively from the same individual (DOI: 10.34425/zs000693).
TIG-3TD is a TERT-immortalised cell line of TIG-3 (Cellosaurus).

name: KP-1NL
comments:
KP-1N has been shown to be a derivative of PANC-1. 
KP-1NL is a subline of KP-1N (ICLAC).

name: NCI-H1882
comments: NCI-H1876 & NCI-H1882 & NCI-H1881 have been derived from the same same patient. (NCI-Navy Medical Oncology Brance Cell Line Supplement DOI: 10.1002/jcb.240630505)

name: MOLT-13
comments: MOLT-13 and MOLT-14 are simultaneous sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: OMM2-5
comments: OMM2-5, OMM2-3 and Mel-270 are derived from the same patient (PMID: 28018010).

name: A375_CJ2
comments: SCH772984 resistant subclone of A375. A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.

name: RCC4-emptyvector
comments:
The RCC4-emptyvector cell line was established from RCC4 by stable transfection with an empty expression vector, pcDNA3, conferring neomycin resistance (ECACC). RCC4-emptyvector and RCC4-VHL were derived from the RCC4 cell line by stable transfection with pcDNA3 and pCDNA3-VHL respectively (ECACC). 
SLR24 was shown to be a RCC4 derivative (ICLAC).

name: BJ
comments: The hTERT-immortalized foreskin fibroblast cell line, BJ-5ta, was derived by transfecting the BJ foreskin fibroblast cell line with the pGRN145 hTERT-expressing plasmid (ATCC).

name: LU-134-A
comments: Lines LU-134-A and LU-134-B have been shown to be related (RIKEN).

name: 1321N1
comments:
U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC). 
1321N1 is a subclone of 1181N1 which itself is a subclone of U-118 MG  (ECACC).

name: CTV-1
comments: Allegedly established from the peripheral blood of a 40-year-old man with acute monoblastic leukemia (AML M5) at relapse in 1982 ; however, recent new data suggest derivation from acute lymphoblastic leukemia based on the expression signature (Andersson et al., Leukemia 19: 1042-1050, 2005, DSMZ).

name: HX
comments:
HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).

name: KMS-28-PE
comments: KMS-28-PE and KMS-28-BM were both derived independent samples, pleural effusion and bone marrow, from the same patient (PMID: 11886382).

name: IM-9
comments: Although derived from the blood of a patient with multiple myeloma this line has been shown to be an EBV-transformed B lymphoblastoid cell line (ATCC).

name: Hs-688A-T
comments: Hs-688A-T was derived from the primary tumour and Hs-688B-T was derived from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient. (ATCC).

name: RMZ-RC5
comments: RMZ-RC2 and RMZ-RC5 are clonal cell lines derived from RMZ (DOI: 10.1038/bjc.1986.273).

name: OCI-Ly13-2
comments:
OCI-Ly13-1 and OCI-Ly13-2 were derived from the same patient. 
OCI-Ly13-1 was established from a sample taken at diagnosis whereas OCI-Ly13-2 was established from a sample obtained during relapse (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V69.5.1307.1307).

name: PANC-1
comments:
KP-1N has been shown to be a derivative of PANC-1. 
KP-1NL is a subline of KP-1N (ICLAC).

name: NCI-H2122
comments: NCI-BL2122 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2122 (ATCC).

name: D-425MED
comments: D-425MED and D-458MED are derived from the same patient. (PubMed=1822845).

name: TDL-4
comments:
TDL-4 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji (ICLAC).
NC-37 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji by DNA fingerptrinting (ATCC).

name: HCC1599-BL
comments: HCC1599-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1599 (ATCC).

name: NCI-H1184
comments: NCI-BL1184 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1184. (ATCC)

name: GLC-82
comments:
HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

name: JHH-1
comments: Originally thought to be of human origin but found to be from mouse (PMID: 20143388, Cellosaurus).

name: AU565
comments: AU565 and SK-BR-3 were derived from the same patient (ATCC).

name: COLO-800
comments:
COLO-818 has been shown to come from the same patient as COLO-800 (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.25242.)
COLO-800 and COLO-794 were both derived from the same patient (ECACC).

name: PA-TU-8988T
comments: PA-TU-8988T and PA-TU-8988S are sister cell lines established from the same patient (DSMZ, PMID:1348891).

name: PaCaDD-141
comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

name: JHU-028
comments: JHU-028 has been shown to be cross contaminated with A549 (ICLAC).

name: NCI-H2077
comments: NCI-BL2077 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H2077. (PMID: 8806092)

name: LB647-PBL
comments: LB647-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB647-SCLC.

name: MMAc
comments: MMAc-SF is a serum-free medium adapted version of the MMAc cell line (RIKEN).

name: COR-L23-R
comments: COR-L23-R is a multi-drug resistant sub-line derived from the parent line COR-L23 after treatment with doxorubicin (ECACC).

name: Hs-860-T
comments: Hs-870-T, Hs-860-T and Hs-791-T were derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus, ATCC)

name: NCI-BL1395
comments: NCI-BL1395 is a lymphoblastoid line established from the same patient as NCI-H1395 (ATCC).

name: OPM-1
comments: OPM-1 and OPM-2 were established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 3926660).

name: CI
comments: Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) immortalized. CI formerly thought of as a B-lymphoblastoid sister of CII is now deemed a subclone of CII. (DSMZ)

name: AZ-521
comments: AZ-521 was originally reported as a human gastric cancer cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of AZ-521 is identical to the HuTu-80 cell line which was derived from a human duodenum carcinoma (JCRB).

name: WIL2-S
comments: WIL2-S is a HAT sensitive variant of the WIL2-NS cell line (ATCC).

name: LU-99A
comments: LU-99A is a subclone of LU-99.

name: EHEB
comments: Suspected to be a  B-lymphoblastoid cell line rather than a bona fide B-CLL cell line (DSMZ, PMID: 12592342).

name: JURL-MK1
comments: JURL-MK1 and JURL-MK2 are sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

name: HCC1428
comments: HCC1428-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as the breast carcinoma cell line HCC1428 (ATCC).

name: Jurkat
comments:
J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

name: KP-3
comments:
KP-3L cells were established using tumor nodules removed from the liver of mouse that had KP-3 cells injected into the spleen (JCRB).
KP-3N was derived from parent line KP-3 (PMID: 2172194).

name: HEL
comments: HEL and HEL-92-1-7 share common ancestry (PMID: 25877200).
